  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research contexts to assess CFD-predicted hemolysis levels for a centrifugal blood pump operating under ventricular assist device conditions. The computational model targets absolute hemolysis index prediction at Model Risk Level 5 for a Class III device. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; six remain flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite the gaps, the assessed factors collectively satisfy the required credibility thresholds under the Minimal profile declaration, and the decision record reflects conditional acceptance pending resolution of the outstanding epistemic uncertainties. No structured Context of Use object is attached to this package; the intended-use scope is conveyed through this narrative description alone.",
